text:
Hi Antonio!

As a general rule, you can't expect that different OS will schedule
threads the same way. Even the same OS may be different at times, when
under significant load, etc.

You can try some more tests:
- Add Inkey(0) at the end of Main()
- If you always want to wait, then the second thread should have similar
construct:

function Another()
  local pThread := hb_ThreadStart( @OneMore() )

  if hb_threadWait( pThread, 15 ) != 1
    hb_threadQuitRequest( pThread )
  endif
  ? "From another"

return nil

Best regards, Aleksander
